00:08:44,850 --> 00:08:48,050
Tokyo,
Adachi-ku,
Kobayashi
0-00-0

111
00:08:45,380 --> 00:08:48,030
I'm Amamiya from Sanpou Sports.

112
00:08:48,560 --> 00:08:49,930
Hello.

113
00:08:51,550 --> 00:08:53,520
Mr. Amamiya...?

114
00:08:56,910 --> 00:08:59,320
A memory from a snowy day ?

115
00:09:00,250 --> 00:09:04,280
I think that's what it is, 
but I can't remember.

116
00:09:05,460 --> 00:09:06,550
A snowball fight.

117
00:09:07,690 --> 00:09:08,850
That's not it.

118
00:09:08,850 --> 00:09:10,000
You made a snow hut.

119
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:11,910
That's not it, either.

120
00:09:12,870 --> 00:09:17,310
Is it about when we drew pictures in the snow with our pee ?

121
00:09:17,310 --> 00:09:18,970
That's definitely not it at all.

122
00:09:21,690 --> 00:09:23,150
Is it about Hikari ?

123
00:09:25,220 --> 00:09:28,380
Um, well, it's probably nothing.

124
00:09:31,450 --> 00:09:33,800
I hope it'll accumulate.

125
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:35,530
If it does, you might remember.

126
00:09:36,730 --> 00:09:39,720
Moron ! We won't be
 able to practice if it does !

127
00:09:40,780 --> 00:09:42,100
That's true.

128
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:49,210
But today will also be a 
memorable day, wrapped up in snow.

129
00:09:50,150 --> 00:09:52,400
Really, it's nothing.

130
00:10:05,550 --> 00:10:08,010
That's what I said, 
but it bothers me.

131
00:10:11,750 --> 00:10:14,160
Crap !

132
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:21,350
Hiro, you have a phone call !

133
00:10:26,850 --> 00:10:28,110
Hikari's essay ?

134
00:10:28,110 --> 00:10:32,080
When Haruka mentioned 
Hikari's name, I remembered.

135
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:36,000
Something about snow, and the elm.

136
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:39,020
She wrote something about that.

137
00:10:39,020 --> 00:10:40,400
That must be it !

138
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:43,140
Can't you find it in the 
graduation essay collection ?

139
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:47,770
I can't read mine because of the scribbles you made.

140
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:51,990
Wait.

141
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:56,500
Found it.

142
00:10:56,550 --> 00:11:00,500
Amamiya Hikari

Memories of 
Elementary School

143
00:10:58,100 --> 00:10:59,600
Maybe not.

144
00:11:02,750 --> 00:11:06,100
This might be it. You remember that we buried a time capsule, right ?

145
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:10,570
Didn't we put "My Treasure" into it ?

146
00:11:10,570 --> 00:11:11,420
Huh ?

147
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:18,410
You put a ball in. I put a cap in. 
And I think Hikari put her essay in it.

148
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:21,800
Do you want to 
dig it up and see it ?

149
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:26,750
Moron ! That's meant to 
be a present for future kids.

150
00:11:26,750 --> 00:11:28,380
Then there's only one way.

151
00:11:29,390 --> 00:11:34,200
If you want to know what's in that essay, you should just ask Hikari.

152
00:11:36,530 --> 00:11:38,640
It's nothing important.

153
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:41,840
It's not worth asking her about.

154
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:43,120
Just forget about it.

155
00:11:44,490 --> 00:11:47,050
Well, even if they're
 not the tastiest things...

156
00:11:47,050 --> 00:11:51,440
...you get nostalgic about cheap snacks and you somehow feel like eating them.

