It's nothing important.

162
00:12:31,310 --> 00:12:34,610
It's not worth asking her about.

163
00:12:34,610 --> 00:12:35,600
Just forget about it.

164
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,300
It's cold.

165
00:12:50,230 --> 00:12:51,160
Hey.

166
00:12:54,540 --> 00:12:56,050
You're playing pachinko again ?

167
00:12:56,050 --> 00:12:57,980
What do you mean "again" ?

168
00:12:57,980 --> 00:13:03,190
I always see you near a pachinko place or a bar.

169
00:13:03,190 --> 00:13:06,180
I've only seen you tending the store once or twice.

170
00:13:06,180 --> 00:13:08,340
That's not nice to say.

171
00:13:09,130 --> 00:13:10,400
I get up early in the morning...

172
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:14,080
...open the boxes of books delivered to us, and display them in the store.

173
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:19,510
And after everyone goes to sleep,
 I organize the receipts and do bookkeeping.

174
00:13:19,510 --> 00:13:21,490
Man, I'm so busy.

175
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:24,300
Why don't you do all those things during the day...

176
00:13:24,300 --> 00:13:26,750
...when you're otherwise just dawdling around ?

177
00:13:26,750 --> 00:13:29,540
Pachinko places would close, you know ?

178
00:13:29,540 --> 00:13:32,970
Pachinko places are open late, too.

179
00:13:32,970 --> 00:13:35,700
In the evening hours, 
the good slots are all taken.

180
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:41,090
Oh, well. Because you're hardly ever home, people think that you've left.

181
00:13:41,090 --> 00:13:42,790
Don't be silly.

182
00:13:42,790 --> 00:13:47,530
Then do you know what Hikari's treasure
 was when she was in elementary school ?

183
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:55,110
Well, why don't you come to our
house for a cup of tea, for once ?

184
00:13:55,110 --> 00:13:58,550
I always stop by your house.
You're just hardly ever there.

185
00:13:58,190 --> 00:13:58,670
It's just that you're hardly ever there.

186
00:13:58,550 --> 00:14:00,230
Really ?

187
00:14:01,050 --> 00:14:06,500
Amamiya

188
00:14:05,380 --> 00:14:06,370
Oh, how rare.

189
00:14:07,370 --> 00:14:09,280
You're such a liar.

190
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:11,760
What do you mean, 
"I always stop by your house" ?

191
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:13,900
"How rare," she says.

192
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:15,800
I was talking about you, Dad.

193
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:17,060
Oh, I see.

194
00:14:17,510 --> 00:14:19,460
Oh, Uncle is here.

195
00:14:20,810 --> 00:14:22,780
Takaaki is here ?

196
00:14:22,780 --> 00:14:24,370
It's been a while.

197
00:14:26,780 --> 00:14:29,950
Takaaki is a newspaper reporter, right ?

198
00:14:29,950 --> 00:14:34,570
Yeah, he's going back to the
 main office in Tokyo next year.

199
00:14:34,990 --> 00:14:35,800
Oh.

200
00:14:40,670 --> 00:14:42,770
Hey, Hiro, come here !

201
00:14:43,630 --> 00:14:44,650
Sure.

202
00:14:45,580 --> 00:14:46,740
Good evening.

203
00:14:46,740 --> 00:14:50,550
Hiro, you've grown.

204
00:14:52,560 --> 00:14:55,920
What happened to baseball ? 
Are you still playing ?

205
00:14:55,920 --> 00:14:57,470
Yes.

206
00:14:57,470 --> 00:14:59,160
Which school do you go to ?

207
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:00,540
It's Senkawa.

208
00:15:00,540 --> 00:15:01,970
Senkawa ?

209
00:15:12,130 --> 00:15:14,450
Their baseball club was 
established just recently.

210
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:16,770
Oh, is that true ?

211
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:18,020
Yes, it is.

212
00:15:19,650 --> 00:15:25,330
Speaking of which, I just went to see Meiwa, the leading candidate for the Invitational.

213
00:15:25,330 --> 00:15:27,250
So he says.

214
00:15:27,250 --> 00:15:31,180
That guy, Tachibana Hideo, lives up to his reputation.

215
00:15:31,180 --> 00:15:35,060
I think he's going to be a star player 
who will get people to come to the park.

216
00:15:35,060 --> 00:15:36,450
So he says.

217
00:15:36,450 --> 00:15:37,260
Yup.

218
00:15:37,610 --> 00:15:41,330
He's smart, and he's thoughtful.

219
00:15:41,330 --> 00:15:43,450
He'll do well in 
professional baseball, too.

220
00:15:44,580 --> 00:15:48,690
If it's about Tachibana, it's 
way easier to just ask Hikari.

221
00:15:49,070 --> 00:15:50,360
Huh ?

222
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:56,000
I just remembered.

223
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,760
Remembered what ?

224
00:15:57,760 --> 00:16:02,500
The essay you wrote in elementary school, about your dream for the future.

225
00:16:10,050 --> 00:16:13,400
It was to become a
 newspaper reporter, right ?

226
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:15,530
Yeah, a sports reporter.

227
00:16:15,530 --> 00:16:16,300
That's right.

228
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:45,700
Wednesday, May 21st

229
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:45,700
Class Newspaper

230
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:45,700
This Week's Kunimi and Noda

231
00:16:45,700 --> 00:16:50,600
This Week's Kunimi and Noda
He threw 70 meters !

232
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:58,000
Like that elm tree, I'd like to be
 someone who will never change.

233
00:17:00,650 --> 00:17:01,250
Can it be...?

234
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:05,120
Can it be what ?

235
00:17:05,120 --> 00:17:07,450
Is that still what you want to do ?

236
00:17:07,450 --> 00:17:09,250
You think it's impossible, don't you ?

237
00:17:10,020 --> 00:17:11,000
No.

238
00:17:13,150 --> 00:17:14,760
I think you can do it.

239
00:17:15,850 --> 00:17:19,260
When I told Hide-chan about it, he didn't take me seriously.

240
00:17:20,370 --> 00:17:24,190
It's because you never
 show your true self to Hideo.

241
00:17:24,700 --> 00:17:25,410
Huh ?

242
00:17:26,230 --> 00:17:30,900
When you're with him,
 you act like a docile, nice girl.

243
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:38,450
Hideo doesn't know how 
stubborn or strong-willed you are.

244
00:17:38,870 --> 00:17:40,000
Hmm.

245
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:46,100
Boys want to show their good sides when they're with girls, too, right ?

246
00:17:46,990 --> 00:17:51,240
If you don't show him your true character from time to time, it'll be stressful.

247
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:52,460
Oh ?

248
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:57,410
Didn't you say you're done playing the go-between ?

249
00:17:58,340 --> 00:18:00,120
Hmm...

250
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:05,120
Hikari and Tachibana Hideo...

251
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:06,500
Are you surprised ?

252
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:13,120
Well, I have no complaint about it.

253
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:15,970
But as a pair, 
it feels a bit strange.

254
00:18:15,970 --> 00:18:18,000
Is that a news reporter's intuition ?

255
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:21,130
Well, it's not anything reliable.

256
00:18:21,130 --> 00:18:25,720
My image of Hikari is that of her when 
she was in elementary school, after all.

257
00:18:25,720 --> 00:18:26,880
I see.

258
00:18:36,590 --> 00:18:37,500
It's cold.

259
00:18:39,810 --> 00:18:41,130
My treasure...

260
00:18:41,940 --> 00:18:43,470
...is my dream.

261
00:18:46,970 --> 00:18:48,800
Memories are memories.

262
00:18:52,870 --> 00:18:53,780
I'm home.

263
00:18:56,040 --> 00:18:57,860
Oh, he's home now ! 
He's home now !

264
00:19:02,510 --> 00:19:03,800
Hey, moronic son.

265
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:06,510
You have a phone call from the company president's daughter.

266
00:19:08,380 --> 00:19:09,450
What's up ?

267
00:19:10,050 --> 00:19:11,000
Hey !

268
00:19:11,940 --> 00:19:15,040
The snow is beautiful ? 
Are you a moron ?

